{
  "stem": "10588.8",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is a little poem that I wrote.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's one of my shortest poem.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's written February 10, 1978.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's called 'My Love Belongs to All.' 'My body belongs to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To God belongs my soul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To my children belongs my inheritance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My love belongs to all.' At the gate of Auschwitz, I didn't say goodbye to my family.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my mother's last words was, Itkalo, I have to go with the little children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I cannot leave them alone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But remember, my child, no matter what happen, don't become hateful and bitter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I understand now, that when you hate others, when you're prejudice, you destroy yourself and others in the process.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I resisted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my love belongs to all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I am outrage of what the Nazis did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I will not let them destroy me by carrying hatred in my soul.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because you cannot be free when you hate others.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I came to the hospital, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I felt very alone, very isolated, and very moved by the kindness of the people in contrast to what they did to us in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But at the same token, I didn't know a world of English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was a stranger in a strange land.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wanted to preserve badly my own customs and traditions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I had to learn a new language and everything anew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I couldn't understand the language.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was the language barrier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I realized how important languages are.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even in Auschwitz, if it wouldn't be that I knew when they gave an order, what it meant more or less, I would have beaten probably more.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I obeyed the orders because I knew if I don't, that I can be killed.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
